body:
## STR

this occurs on stable & nightly.

```Rust
macro_rules! m {
    ($s: path) => {{
        Some($s {})
    }}
}

struct S {}
fn main() {
    let _ = m!(S);
}
```

## Expected Result

Code compiles, e.g. it compiles if the macro doesn't contain a `Some`:
```Rust
macro_rules! m {
    ($s: path) => {{
        $s {}
    }}
}
```

## Actual Result

Obscure parser error

```
error: expected one of `)`, `,`, `.`, `?`, or an operator, found `{`
 --> src/main.rs:3:17
  |
3 |         Some($s {})
  |                 ^ expected one of `)`, `,`, `.`, `?`, or an operator here
...
9 |     let _ = m!(S);
  |             ----- in this macro invocation

error: aborting due to previous error
```

cc @dtolnay @estebank @petrochenkov 

@nikomatsakis & @eddyb : this frustrates me lifting `TypeFoldable` over `Result`
